<worksheet label="ws-act-exp-log-properties-exp-or-log">
  <activity xml:id="act-exp-log-properties-exp-or-log">
    <introduction>
      <p>
			In the questions that follow, we compare and contrast the properties and behaviors of exponential and logarithmic functions. 
		</p>
      <p/>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-exp-log-properties-exp-or-log-task-0">
      <statement>
        <p>
						Let <m>f(t) = 1 - e^{-(t-1)}</m> and <m>g(t) = \ln(t)</m>.  Plot each function on the same set of coordinate axes.  What properties do the two functions have in common?  For what properties do the two functions differ?  Consider each function's domain, range, <m>t</m>-intercept, <m>y</m>-intercept, increasing/decreasing behavior, concavity, and long-term behavior.
					</p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer/>
      <solution/>
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-exp-log-properties-exp-or-log-task-1">
      <statement>
        <p>
						Let <m>h(t) = a - be^{-k(t-c)}</m>, where <m>a</m>, <m>b</m>, <m>c</m>, and <m>k</m> are positive constants.  Describe <m>h</m> as a transformation of the function <m>E(t) = e^t</m>.
					</p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer/>
      <solution/>
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-exp-log-properties-exp-or-log-task-2">
      <statement>
        <p>
						Let <m>r(t) = a + b\ln(t-c)</m>, where <m>a</m>, <m>b</m>, and <m>c</m> are positive constants.  Describe <m>r</m> as a transformation of the function <m>L(t) = \ln(t)</m>.
					</p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer/>
      <solution/>
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-exp-log-properties-exp-or-log-task-3">
      <statement>
        <p>
				      Data for the height of a tree is given in the <xref ref="T-log-act-tree">Table</xref>;
				      time <m>t</m> is measured in years and height is given in feet.  At <url href="http://gvsu.edu/s/0yy">http://gvsu.edu/s/0yy</url>, you can find a <em>Desmos</em> worksheet with this data already input.
				    </p>
        <table xml:id="T-log-act-tree">
          <title>The height of a tree as a function of time <m>t</m> in years.</title>
