        <p>
						Do you think this data is better modeled by a logarithmic function of form <m>p(t) = a + b\ln(t-c)</m> or by an exponential function of form <m>q(t) = m + ne^{-rt}</m>.  Provide reasons based in how the data appears and how you think a tree grows, as well as by experimenting with sliders appropriately in <em>Desmos</em>.  (Note: you may need to adjust the upper and lower bounds of several of the sliders in order to match the data well.)
					</p>
